	   <tr><td colspan=2>Agility increases your armor class slightly - it adds to the avoidance portion of your AC.&nbsp;&nbsp;That's it.  So, yes, it does reduce your chance to get hit from that aspect.  BUT, it does not affect your chance to block/dodge/riposte.  Only your skill in those skills affects your success rate.  So, you can quantify agility's benefit to you by its effect on your AC, and that being the case you can tell when one piece of gear is better than another by merely observing your AC change.  Agi gives smaller returns than straight AC/HP.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
